    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        King</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 48.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Excuse me for reminding you of a regulation of
                    this department. Every despatch should be confined to one subject alone. If
                    several subjects are to be treated of, they should be made the bases of distinct
                    despatches. This regulation has its foundation in the necessity which exists for
                    having always convenient references to the records and archives of the
                    department.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rufus King,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
